✈️ FlightFinder Project

🧱 Project Structure Overview


---

📁 Folder and File Structure (Node.js Example)

FlightFinder/
├── client/                  # Frontend code
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── styles.css
│   └── script.js
│
├── server/                  # Backend code
│   ├── controllers/
│   │   └── flightController.js
│   ├── models/
│   │   └── flightModel.js
│   ├── routes/
│   │   └── flightRoutes.js
│   ├── config/
│   │   └── db.js
│   └── app.js               # Main server file
│
├── .env                     # Environment variables
├── package.json             # Project metadata and dependencies
└── README.md                # Project documentation


---

🧩 Components Breakdown

🔹 Frontend (client/)

index.html: Main HTML page to interact with users

styles.css: Styling and layout

script.js: Logic to fetch and display flight data


🔹 Backend (server/)

controllers/: Handles logic for processing requests

routes/: Manages API endpoints (e.g., /api/flights)

models/: Contains database schema definitions

config/: Stores DB connection settings

app.js: Initializes the server and connects all parts


🔹 Database

flight table: Stores flight details

user table: Stores user info

booking table: Stores booking records

payment table: Tracks transactions



---

🌐 Example API Endpoints

Method	Endpoint	Description

GET	/api/flights	Fetch all flights
POST	/api/book	Book a flight
POST	/api/payment	Process payment
